<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-215] addIndexes unexpectedly closes index</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-215</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;It seems that in 1.4rc2, a call to IndexWriter.addIndexes (IndexReader[]) will&lt;br/&gt;
close the provided IndexReader; in 1.3-final this does not happen.  So my code&lt;br/&gt;
which uses addIndexes to merge new information into an index and then calls&lt;br/&gt;
close() on the IndexReader now crashes with an &quot;already closed&quot; exception.  I&lt;br/&gt;
can attach test code which works in 1.3 but not in 1.4rc2 if that would be helpful.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If this is an intentional change in behavior, it needs to be documented.  Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Operating System: Linux&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: Other&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
